                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_bællyn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>bællyn</orth><form type="participle"><orth>bællyd</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>bællun</orth><form type="participle"><orth>bæld</orth></form></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>стремиться к чему</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>aspire</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>желать чего</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>wish something</q></abv:tr></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>bællic</orth></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>стремление</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>aspiration</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>желание</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>wish</q></abv:tr></sense></sense></re><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>cardæn jæ k˳ystmæ bællydtæn zærdiagæj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>к труду жизни я стремился всем сердцем</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>I was aspiring with all my heart to the work of my life</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>ma babæll wællagmæ!</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>не прельстись верхней (дорогой)!</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>do not be attracted by the upper (road)!</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>70</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>i qalti cardmæ necæmæj bælldtæj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>он нисколько не соблазнялся жизнью спесивых (богатых)</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>he did not become tempted at all by the life of haughty (rich) ones</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes."/><biblScope>104</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Возводится к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*var-</w> <gloss><q>желать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/> <gloss><q>выбирать</q></gloss></mentioned> с необычным развитием начального %iv%i → %ib%i (cp., однако, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bar"/> ‘право’, ‘воля’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_byjyn"/> ‘вить’). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>var-</w> <gloss><q>выбирать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>предпочитать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>var-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>vṛnoti</w> <gloss><q>предпочитает</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>желает</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>любит</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/> <w>вѣлети</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><w>воля</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>велеть</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>воля</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/> <w>vêlyti</w> <gloss><q>желать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/> <w>wellan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>wollen</w> <gloss><q>желать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>volo</w> <gloss><q>я хочу</q></gloss></mentioned>. Для объяснения осетинской формы приходится исходить из усиленной основы %ivarya%i--, в этом случае %ir%i перед %iу%i закономерно дал %il%i, а геминация %ily%i →%ill%i (как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_allon"/> из %iāryana%i и др.); ср. основу %ivarya%i- в таких образованиях, как <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>varya-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>vairya-</w> <gloss><q>желанный</q></gloss></mentioned>. В ближайшем родстве с %ibællyn%i стоят <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bar"/> ‘воля’, ‘право’ и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bærgæ"/> ‘хотя’; в более отдаленном — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wyrnyn"/> ‘верить’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>245</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*var-</w> <gloss><q>wish</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/> <gloss><q>choose</q></gloss></mentioned> with the unusual development of the initial %iv%i → %ib%i (cf., however, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bar"/> ‘right’, ‘will’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_byjyn"/> ‘wind’). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>var-</w> <gloss><q>choose</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>prefer</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>var-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>vṛnoti</w> <gloss><q>s/he prefers</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>s/he wishes</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>s/he loves</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/> <w>věleti</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><w>volya</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>velet'</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>volya</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/> <w>vêlyti</w> <gloss><q>wish</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/> <w>wellan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>wollen</w> <gloss><q>wish</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>volo</w> <gloss><q>I want</q></gloss></mentioned>. For explaining of the Ossetic form we have to start from a %bstrong%b stem %ivarya%i-; in this case %ir%i before %iу%i turned into a regular %il%i, and the gemination %ily%i →%ill%i (like <ref type="xr" target="#entry_allon"/> derived from %iāryana%i etc.); cf. the stem %ivarya%i- in such derivations as: <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>varya-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>vairya-</w> <gloss><q>desired</q></gloss></mentioned>. The following words are close related to the word %ibællyn%i: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bar"/> ‘will’, ‘right’ and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bærgæ"/> ‘although’; in a less related word <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wyrnyn"/> ‘believe’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>245</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>